Pop a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the noodles. Halve the @green pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @carrot{1} (no need to peel), then grate on the coarse side of your #grater{}. Chop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} into thirds. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2}, Tenderstem® broccoli and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water. Return to the #pan{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop them from sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the onion and pepper. Stir-fry until beginning to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Next, add the garlic and @ginger puree{1}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @teriyaki sauce{150%g} into the pan and stir to coat all the veggies. Lower the heat and cook until everything is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the grated carrot and noodles to the pan and toss or stir to combine. Stir-fry until everything is piping hot, ~{2%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you need to loosen it up a bit.

Share the noodles between your plates and finish with a sprinkle of chopped peanuts. Enjoy!